    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on </span><span class=\"english\">‘Purpose of Dream’</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\">10</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Purpose of Dream</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Dreams serve various purposes, both psychological and biological. They help process emotions and experiences, allowing the brain to organize and store memories. By replaying events or creating symbolic narratives, dreams aid in emotional regulation, helpin</span><span class=\"english\">g individuals cope with stress or unresolved feelings. They can also stimulate creativity, providing solutions to problems or inspiring new ideas. Some theories suggest that dreams play a role in rehearsing potential threats, preparing the dreamer for real</span><span class=\"english\">-life challenges. Biologically, dreams may assist in brain development and cognitive functioning. During sleep, the brain stays active and dreams may play a role in strengthening and restoring neural connections. While the exact purpose of dreams remains d</span><span class=\"english\">ebated, they are believed to be a crucial aspect of mental and emotional well-being. Dreams also offer insight into the subconscious, revealing hidden fears, desires, and unresolved issues.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------09 </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (Purpose of Dream) </span><span class=\"english\">---------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> --------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Dreams assist in processing emotions and experiences, enabling the brain to organize and store memories.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Purpose of Dream</span><span class=\"english\">) Any 04 points students will get (4×1.5)--------06    <br/>‎</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">1</span><span class=\"english\">. Dreams help individuals cope with stress or unresolved feelings by replaying events or creating symbolic narratives.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. Dreams can stimulate creativity, offering solutions to problems or inspiring new ideas.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3</span><span class=\"english\">. Some theories suggest dreams allow the brain to rehearse potential threats, preparing the dreamer for real-life challenges.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4</span><span class=\"english\">. Biologically, dreams may support brain development and enhance cognitive processes.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">5</span><span class=\"english\">. During sleep, the brain remains active; dreaming may help strengthen and restore neural connections.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">6</span><span class=\"english\">. Though the exact purpose of dreams is still debated, they are widely believed to be crucial for psychological health.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------01 </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Dreams also offer insight into the subconscious, revealing hidden fears, desires, and unresolved issues.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every</span><span class=\"english\">03</span><span class=\"english\">spelling/grammatical mistakes, </span><span class=\"english\">01 mark </span><span class=\"english\">has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para).</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a meaningful sentence with each of the following words</span><span class=\"english\">:</span><span> </span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>5</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Materialize, </span><span class=\"english\">Consider</span><span class=\"english\">, Unreal</span><span class=\"english\">, Fragment,</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Psychotherapy</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Materialize = With dedication and perseverance, their ambitious plans began to </span><span class=\"english\">materialize</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Consider = The committee will </span><span class=\"english\">consider</span><span class=\"english\"> your application once all required documents have been submitted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Unreal = The sunset over the mountains was so beautiful, it felt almost </span><span class=\"english\">unreal</span><span class=\"english\">. </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Fragment</span><span class=\"english\"> = Memories of their trip together lingered in her mind like </span><span class=\"english\">fragments</span><span class=\"english\"> of a beautiful dream.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Psychotherapy = </span><span class=\"english\">Some believe dreams act as </span><span class=\"english\">psychotherapy</span><span class=\"english\">, helping us deal with emotions.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions: </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(i)</span><span class=\"english\"> Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. (Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For </span><span class=\"english\">02</span><span class=\"english\"> spelling mistakes, </span><span class=\"english\">01 mark</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted, for 01 spelling mistake, </span><span class=\"english\">0.5 marks</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted from that very sentence.</span></p><p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">(iv)</span><span class=\"english\"> For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a </span><span class=\"english\">suffix or prefix</span><span class=\"english\">, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the </span><span class=\"english\">subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number</span><span class=\"english\">, etc.).</span></p><p><span class=\"english\"> Comment: </span><span class=\"english\">Use the given word without changing its parts of speech</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p>"
